cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with analyzing deep visual representations for image distortions. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with image quality assessment and characterization of distortion types and severity levels. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses deep neural networks for feature extraction and analysis. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with unsupervised learning of image distortions. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing and characterizing image distortions, which can be useful in image retrieval applications.
